      "desc": "Attending veterinarian and adequate veterinary care (dealers and exhibitors).",
      "narrative": "The facility is administering an expired eye medication to a female African elephant named Lungile. The elephant\nreceived the medication daily since date of expiration of 26 January 2026. A facility representative stated that the\nelephant's eye exam on 19 February 2026 revealed that the defect being treated was gone. The use of expired\nmedications and medical products is not an appropriate method to treat diseases and injuries in animals and may delay\nhealing. Each exhibitor shall establish and maintain programs of adequate veterinary care that include the use of\nappropriate methods to control and treat diseases and injuries.\nCorrected at time of inspection. Correct from this date forward of 25 February 2026.\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with the facility representatives.\nn"
    }
  ],
  "narrative": "2.40(b)(2) \n   \nAttending veterinarian and adequate veterinary care (dealers and exhibitors). \nThe facility is administering an expired eye medication to a female African elephant named Lungile. The elephant \nreceived the medication daily since date of expiration of 26 January 2026. A facility representative stated that the \nelephant's eye exam on 19 February 2026 revealed that the defect being treated was gone. The use of expired \nmedications and medical products is not an appropriate method to treat diseases and injuries in animals and may delay \nhealing. Each exhibitor shall establish and maintain programs of adequate veterinary care that include the use of \nappropriate methods to control and treat diseases and injuries.  \n \nCorrected at time of inspection. Correct from this date forward of 25 February 2026. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with the facility representatives. \n \n n",
